{
  "page": "North Grove",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <p>This article is about content invented for <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_A_Telltale_Games_Series\" title=\"Game of Thrones - A Telltale Games Series\">Game of Thrones - A Telltale Games Series</a></i>, a graphic adventure video game developed by Telltale Games. Although this is a licensed derivative work based upon HBO's <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i> television adaptation of <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>, it is not written by him or the creators of the TV show.</p>\n<p>The material on this page should <i>not</i> be considered canonical for the TV show or the novels, and is provided for informational purposes only.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>North Grove</b> is a place <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>, and is known only to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Forrester\" title=\"House Forrester\">House Forrester</a> south of the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>. It has only appeared in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_A_Telltale_Games_Series\" title=\"Game of Thrones - A Telltale Games Series\">Game of Thrones - A Telltale Games Series</a></i>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=North_Grove&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Forrester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gregor Forrester\">Gregor Forrester</a> sent away his <a href=\"/index.php/Bastardy\" title=\"Bastardy\">bastard</a> children, <a href=\"/index.php/Josera_Snow\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Josera Snow\">Josera</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Elsera_Snow\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Elsera Snow\">Elsera Snow</a>, and they came to the North Grove to cultivate their gifts as a <a href=\"/index.php/Skinchanger\" title=\"Skinchanger\">skinchanger</a> and a <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodmage\" title=\"Bloodmage\">bloodmage</a>, respectively. Josera thought that their father sent them away out of shame, but Elsera believed that they had been sent away for their own protection.\n</p><p>When Lord Gregor was mortally wounded and dying, he asked <a href=\"/index.php/Gared_Tuttle\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gared Tuttle\">Gared Tuttle</a> to see that the North Grove would not be lost. Gared's uncle <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_Tuttle\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Duncan Tuttle\">Duncan</a> had heard of the place, but few others had. Eventually, Gared, <a href=\"/index.php/Cotter\" title=\"Cotter\">Cotter</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php?title=Sylvi&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Sylvi (page does not exist)\">Sylvi</a> reached North Grove after venturing north of the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>, before <a href=\"/index.php/Wights\" title=\"Wights\">wights</a> attacked. Based on player choice, Gared would either choose to stay and protect the North Grove or return to the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> with Josera and Elsera.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=North_Grove&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_A_Telltale_Games_Series\" title=\"Game of Thrones - A Telltale Games Series\">Game of Thrones - A Telltale Games Series</a></i></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible uncollapsed navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;width:100%;color:inherit;;;\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" style=\";\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist\" style=\"display:block;float:left;font-weight:normal;font-size:88%;padding-top:3px;text-align:left;width:6.8em;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/index.php/Template:Region_Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Template:Region Beyond the Wall\"><span title=\"View this template\" style=\";;background:none transparent;border:none;\">v</span></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/index.php?title=Template_talk:Region_Beyond_the_Wall&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Template talk:Region Beyond the Wall (page does not exist)\"><span title=\"Discuss this template\" style=\";;background:none transpare